president steven c beering was tame and designed to spark 
discussion about the right to display controversial art 
theres a lot more art that is done that is more explicit 
loewenstein said 
beering did not pose for the painting nor has he made a public 
statement about it 
i wanted to do something provocative and see how people would 
align themselves while at the same time doing something risky fun 
and mischievous he said it doesnt happen enough at purdue 
gary sudano director of purdues department of creative arts 
removed the painting from a campus art gallery after loewenstein 
refused to withdraw it 
we have exhibition space in our buildings which is reserved 
for the display of works of art that arise from the instructional 
program sudano said thursday we dont provide a forum for 
public displays of personal points of view thats not our 
mission 
sudano said loewenstein has other paintings on display in the 
three campus galleries but all were from classes the student had 
taken 
