tens of thousands of troops from europe along with tank divisions 
and other weapons 
soviet foreign minister eduard a shevardnadze will hold talks 
with baker at the state department next wednesday through friday in 
preparation for a bushgorbachev summit meeting in washington in 
june 
bush and baker clearly are banking on the proposition that they 
can maintain good relations without sacrificing lithuanian 
independence 
nobody denies their right of selfdetermination sergei 
chetverikov ministercounselor of the soviet embassy said tuesday 
and he told reporters the basic premise behind the actions 
of the soviet union is not to use force but to find peaceful 
ways 
the soviet diplomat an expert on constitutional law 
acknowledged however that the situation is difficult 
it is also difficult for bush and baker who have been accused 
in the past of taking too soft an approach to china after the 
suppression of prodemocracy forces last june for instance 
bush has wavered between a conservative and a moderate stance 
throughout his political career rightwing republicans savored his 
attack on liberals during the 1988 presidential campaign against 
gov michael dukakis of massachusetts but they still are checking 
his credentials 
baker bushs guru during the campaign also is suspected of 
being too pragmatic of being inclined to put solutions ahead of 
ideology 
indeed there is a strong element of pragmatism in the policy 
the administration is pursuing on lithuania but it also may 
succeed without hurting either the lithuanians or ussoviet 
relations 
