with a certain bloodalcohol level kentucky is one of just a 
handful of states not to have such wording in their drunkendriving 
law instead drivers in the state are merely presumed to be drunk 
when their bloodalcohol reading reaches 10 percent critics say 
such wording makes it easier for people accused of drunken driving 
