the name czechoslovak federative republic was adopted 
thursday night after a daylong discussion in the federal parliament 
and weeks of growing tensions between the czechs and slovaks 
deputies from the czech lands favored the name czechoslovak 
federative republic while slovak deputies wanted a hyphen in 
czechoslovak republic to underline the equal status of the 
two constituent republics 
