collapse of the locust street bridge authorities said 
identities of the three people injured were withheld pending 
notification of relatives said police investigator milo mally 
two switching engines were pulling nine cars on the freight 
train when the third car a covered grain hopper apparently 
derailed and struck a pillar that supported the 74yearold 
viaduct said john bromley a union pacific spokesman 
