danny beagle 
the crusty union leader who first came to prominence when a 
dockworkers walkout led to a bloody general strike in san 
francisco in 1934 was once labeled a communist by the federal 
government authorities tried repeatedly to throw him out of the 
country for alleged communist activities and he once was jailed 
for 20 days as a communist conspirator 
