<TEXT>
after weeks of sporadic clashes a 
ceasefire between rival christian forces collapsed friday in 
thunderous battles that killed at least 38 people and left beirut 
and the surrounding hills in flames 
the fighting began at daybreak and continued without letup past 
midnight 
residents of the metn region overlooking beirut reported heavy 
shelling the residents reached by telephone from cyprus said 
they had been in bomb shelters since dawn 
its allout war again said a police spokesman who cannot 
be named under standing regulations 
a ceasefire had been in effect since march 3 between gen 
michel aouns troops and the rival lebanese forces militia it had 
been violated repeatedly raising fears of renewed warfare but 
none of the previous fighting was as serious as that friday 
the christian forces have been battling since jan 30 for 
control of the christian enclave aoun began the warfare in january 
by moving to crush samir geageas militia the main challenger to 
aouns authority in the christian region 
police said at least 38 people were killed and 65 wounded in 
savage combat friday in the central sector of christian east beirut 
and in the mountains of kesrouan province 20 miles northeast of 
the capital 
since jan 30 at least 814 people have died in the battles 
most have been civilians 
thunderous blasts reverberated across beirut 
schools churches apartments and shops were set ablaze in the 
city and across kesrouan and flames lit the night sky over beirut 
police said scores of houses collapsed on their tenants 
patriarch nasrallah sfeir spiritual head of the maronite 
catholic community of which aoun and geagea are members threatened 
both men with excommunication if fighting did not stop 
this horrific destructive shelling which the army and the 
lebanese forces blame on each other has forced people to flee 
their homes and take shelter in forests sfeir said 
how dare they claim they are defending christian land while 
they are turning it into scorched earth he said the statement 
was broadcast on beirut radio stations 
sfeir also issued an excommunication threat march 2 a day 
before the ceasefire 
geagea responded to sfeirs latest appeal by saying he would 
stop shooting if aoun reciprocated there was no immediate response 
from aoun 
aouns force of 19000 army troops and geageas 6000man 
militia accused each other of destroying the truce 
aouns command said geagea forces tried to attack army positions 
at badaro next to the geagea stronghold of ashrafieh in east 
beirut 
the attackers suffered heavy losses in lives and equipment 
a communique said 
the lebanese forces issued their own communique it said aouns 
troops attacked the mountain village of kleiat in an attempt to 
clear a path way for aouns troops to capture kesrouan province 
the lebanese forces prevented aouns units from accomplishing 
their objectives and succeeded in pushing them aouns units 
almost completely out of kleiat in a counterattack the lebanese 
forces chief spokesman george abdulmassih told the associated 
press 
before the new outbreak of fighting aouns army held a quarter 
of kleiat the rest was under lebanese forces control 
on thursday maronite leaders met in bkirki seat of the 
maronite patriarchate and empowered a mediation committee to 
reopen talks with geagea and aoun for a political solution 
aoun boycotted the meeting geagea attended and said he will 
press for a resolution urging aoun and himself to discuss with 
president elias hrawi an overall settlement of the lebanese crisis 
aoun geagea and hrawi are all maronites the 900000strong 
catholic sect that has dominated government since lebanons 
independence from france in 1943 
the syrianbacked hrawi was elected president by parliament in 
november and given the task of implementing political reforms 
designed to end 15 years of sectarian civil war 
the reforms and election were part of an arab leaguebrokered 
peace treaty endorsed the previous month 
aoun rejects that accord because it does not guarantee the 
withdrawal of 40000 syrian troops deployed in lebanon since 1976 
to quell civil war fighting 
he refuses to recognize hrawi who dismissed aoun as army 
commander and interim prime minister in november the general has 
refused to step down 
geagea recognizes the presidency he has not declared his 
support for the accord which would give the moslems more of a say 
in governing lebanon 
