distributor but was uncomfortable with the informal arrangement 
were the first he said we have to be careful or someone 
could come here and close us down 
he said echos owners want to offer television that is more 
fun mlynarczyk described polish television as too serious 
a lot of guys sitting in arm chairs telling something blah blah 
blah 
marek hamera the program coordinator said it should be 
closer to life everything stateowned tv doesnt do 
after the solidarityled government assumed power last fall 
prime minister tadeusz mazowiecki was under intense public pressure 
to reform state television which one member of parliament called 
the medium that lied the most 
the evening news program was changed and some announcers most 
closely identified with the former communist regime were replaced 
there was criticism when the new director of the state broadcasting 
committee heeded mazowieckis recommendation against a wholesale 
purge 
