control of the airwaves is being drafted 
echotvs owners said they applied for the station two weeks 
after the new head of the state committee was appointed 
when we got the permission we worked nonstop to put the 
station on the air because we were afraid someone would take it 
away zygmunt said a permit for a second station in lublin 
southeast of warsaw is on hold 
efforts to break the government monopoly on nonsatellite 
television also are under way elsewhere in eastern europe 
especially in hungary 
mti the hungarian news agency reported that 80 applications 
for private broadcast stations had been filed but the hungarian 
government has said there should be only three televison channels 
the state already controls two 
