prospects forecasting a bigger loss for this year and a delay in 
this summers planned emergence from bankruptcy reorganization 
eastern said difficulties in rebuilding its strikebattered 
business also meant it would be unable to fulfill a tentative 
agreement to pay unsecured creditors 50 cents on the dollar under 
that accord the unsecured creditors who are owed 980 million 
would receive about 490 million in cash and notes 
the creditors committee privately passed a resolution late 
tuesday authorizing its attorneys to seek the appointment of a 
trustee and to propose a plan of liquidation said sources close to 
the committee who requested anonymity 
the creditors attorneys would take such action if texas air 
refused to cover easterns future operating losses according to 
the resolution 
currently the losses are funded out of escrow accounts held for 
the creditors which contain the proceeds of sales of eastern 
assets 
in the event texas air refuses to fund such losses the 
committee hereby authorizes counsel to prepare and file either a 
motion seeking the appointment of a trustee to consummate the sale 
to american airlines and then to effectuate an orderly liquidation 
