japans consumer price index climbed a steep 36 
percent in february from a year ago as a snap of cold weather 
pushed up food prices while a weak yen caused a rise in wholesale 
prices the government said friday 
the management and coordination agency said februarys 
yeartoyear gain was the largest since november 1981 when 
consumer prices rose 38 percent 
compared with the previous month consumer prices were up 03 
percent 
higher vegetable prices resulting from heavy snow and cold 
weather were largely responsible for last months increase said an 
agency official speaking on condition of anonymity 
vegetable prices jumped 173 percent in february while prices 
for fresh vegetable prices surged 249 percent the agency said 
fruit prices increased by 147 percent and dairy products rose 
108 percent 
recreation expenses registered a 51 percent increase the 
agency said 
in the tokyo area consumer prices were up 04 percent in march 
from the previous month and were 35 percent higher than a year 
earlier the government said tokyoarea prices are seen as an 
early indicator of price movements for the rest of japan 
for the fiscal year ending saturday consumer prices in the 
tokyoarea were up 32 percent from the previous fiscal year 
separately the bank of japan reported wholesale prices edged up 
02 percent in the second 10 days of march from the previous 10day 
period and were up 38 percent from a year earlier 
the central bank attributed the increase partly to the weak 
japanese yen wholesale prices have been rising gradually in recent 
months as the yens steady decline made imports more expensive 
meanwhile japan posted a 4907 billion current account surplus 
in february down 324 percent from a year ago the finance 
ministry reported 
this marked the 12th consecutive decline in the current account 
surplus from yearearlier levels the ministry said 
japans trade surplus registered 5491 billion in february 
down 356 percent drop a year ago exports totaled 215 billion 
down 500 million or 22 percent from a year ago while imports 
climbed 26 billion or 189 percent to 161 billion 
separately the government said the seasonally adjusted 
unemployment rate fell to 21 percent in february as the job market 
continued to tighten 
februarys jobless rate down 01 percentage point from 
januarys 22 percent matched the lowest level japan has 
maintained since last june 
