<TEXT>
here is a rundown of key events in the growth of united parcel 
services airdelivery operations as provided by the company 
aug 28 1907 united parcel service was founded as a messenger 
business in seattle and quickly expanded to delivery of packages 
mostly from department stores to their customers 
feb 15 1929 ups began a limited flying delivery service 
known as united air express serving key pacific coast points 
three arizona cities and el paso texas 
april 13 1931 united air express was terminated in the midst 
of the great depression 
jan 22 1953 ups restarted an air package transportation 
service 
july 6 1953 upsair began twoday service eastboundonly from 
los angeles and san francisco to new yor philadelphia chicago 
portland and seattle service was later extended to westbound and 
included more cities 
july 28 1956 upsair added a special long distance 
transcontinental air service with delivery in four to five days for 
a reduced rate 
april 30 1959 upsair was changed to blue label air 
aug 28 1961 long distance service name was changed to 
brown label 
nov 6 1967 all air service was converted to twoday delivery 
under the blue label name 
march 1 1971 air service was expanded to 31 states 
jan 5 1976 air service was expanded to 49 states 
feb 28 1977 air service was expanded to 50 states 
late 1981early 1982 ups purchased 20 727100 aircraft for 
package delivery use 
aug 23 1982 ups inaugurated next day air service between los 
angeles and san francisco 
sept 20 1982 next day air was extended to 24 metropolitan 
areas and later that year included 37 states plus washington 
oct 3 1983 next day air was extended to 44 states plus 
washington 
aug 6 1984 thirteen cargo jets were purchased for 208 
million bringing total aircraft fleet size to 53 
june 3 1985 next day air was extended to all 48 contiguous 
states puerto rico and hawaii and the next day air letter was 
introduced 
oct 7 1985 international air service began between the 
northeast and six european countries 
sept 15 1986 international air service expanded to 16 
nations 
oct 3 1988 international air service expanded to 41 nations 
aug 24 1989 worldwide air express package and document 
delivery service began expanding network to 175 nations and 
territories 
dec 6 1989 air service extended to eastern europe 
jan 3 1990 first scheduled flight by upsowned aircraft to 
asia 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

