bond prices lost ground friday in light to 
moderate activity reflecting concerns that next weeks economic 
reports may indicate some lingering strength that could keep the 
pressure on interest rates 
the bellwether 30year treasury bond fell rsqb point or 375 for 
every 1000 in face value 
its yield which rises when the price falls climbed to 862 
percent from 858 percent late thursday its yield had been 847 
percent only a week ago 
