federated stores inc the parent company of 
federated department stores inc and allied stores corp on friday 
asked that it be placed under chapter 11 protection of the us 
bankrupty court 
the two subsidiaries filed for similar protection in january 
g william miller chairman and chief executive officer of the 
parent company said the petition was a procedural step to allow 
us to expedite the reorganization planning process 
as the parent company of federated and allied fsi is of 
necessity concerned with the total debt structure of these 
companies as well as in helping to effect a solution to the 
financial difficulties imposed by this structure miller said 
by bringing fsi more directly into the chapter 11 process we 
will be able to approach a reorganizatin solution for federated and 
allied in a consistent and logical manner and in a way that makes 
the most sense for the companies and their creditors 
the parent company whose officers and headquarters are in 
cincinnati said the filing was made in us bankruptcy court in 
san francisco although the federated and allied divisions filed 
their chapter 11 proceedings in us bankrutpcy court in 
cincinnati the parent said it filed in san francisco because that 
court has jurisdiction over other chapter 11 proceedings by some of 
its intermediate holding companies 
allen i questrom chairman and chief executive officer of the 
federated and allied divisions issued a statement aimed at 
separating the action of the parent company from the daytoday 
retail operations 
because todays action by fsi has absolutely no effect 
whatsoever on the ongoing businesses of federated and allied we 
want to avoid any risk of confusion or misunderstanding by assuring 
that the record is set straight from the onset questrom said 
the department store operations of federated and allied remain 
sound and profitable sales are steadily improving and are now 
runing ahead of plan the companies cash position is excellent 
we have stabilized our work force and our organizations our 
employees are receiving all of the pay and benefits to which they 
are entitled and we have returned to normal operations in 
virtually all areas of our business and at all levels of our 
companies across the country 
federated stores formerly known as campeau corp us was 
formed as the us retailing subsidiary of torontobased campeau 
corp which is owned primarily by canadian real estate developer 
robert campeau 
campeau said in a statement friday that it had amended 
agreements with edward j debartolo corp and with two subsidiaries 
