friday 
the agreements require debartolo a major shopping mall 
developer and olympia amp york a real estate concern to refrain 
from taking any collateral they hold in campeau without giving nine 
days notice first the amendment ensures the agreements remain in 
effect despite the chapter 11 filing campeau said 
torontobased olympia amp york helped ease campeaus financial 
difficulties last year through a loan to the company on friday 
campeau said it will not pay interest due saturday on two bond 
issues and wants to defer the payments one of the issues worth 
260 million is owned by olympia amp york the second worth 184 
million canadian dollars is publicly traded 
federated and allied which operate 260 deparment stores in 28 
states filed for bankruptcy protection jan 15 listing 77 
billion in debt 
the federated group includes bloomingdales and abraham and 
straus both based in new york burdines of miami lazarus of 
cincinnati and richs of atlanta 
the allied group includes the bon marche of seattle jordan 
marsh of boston maas brothers of tampa and sterns of paramus 
nj 
campeau acquired allied in 1986 and federated in 1988 largely 
on the basis of borrowed money but federated and allied were 
unable to meet the interest payments on that debt forcing the 
bankruptcy filing 
